# Design reference documentation

When implementing rules, content, classes, ancestries, subclasses, or chargen features, consult these sources **before inventing mechanics or names**.

## In-repo (versioned)

- `docs/design/` — Foundry implementation briefs (vision, resolution, character model, chargen, automation, sheet layout, inventory).
- `docs/playtest-chargen-mvp.md` — QA checklist for chargen MVP.
- `docs/testing.md` — local Foundry playtest setup.

## Local design bible (not in git)

**Path:** `G:/AshandAnvil_Docs/` (also linked at repo root as `AshandAnvil_Docs/` — gitignored).

| Folder / file | Contents |
|---------------|----------|
| `Classes/ash_and_anvil_parent_class_design_draft_expanded.md` | Parent class design draft |
| `Classes/Subclasses/README_class_subclass_index.md` | Index of all subclass docs |
| `Classes/Subclasses/*_subclasses.md` | Per-class subclass options and progression |
| `Races/ash_and_anvil_race_design.md` | Ancestry / race design |

The user adds new markdown under `AshandAnvil_Docs/` over time. Prefer the newest doc in the relevant subfolder over stale in-repo stubs when they conflict; flag conflicts explicitly.

## Usage

- Treat `AshandAnvil_Docs` as **canonical IP and mechanics reference** for names, class structure, subclasses, and ancestries.
- Keep `docs/design/` aligned with what is actually implemented in Foundry; do not copy the full external bible into the repo.
- Never commit files from `AshandAnvil_Docs/` — the folder is gitignored by design.
